JUST as they were about to arrive at the scrapyard, the two men were stopped by cops. Now they are in jail for allegedly stealing copper wire. Police spokesman Captain Sergio Kock said the men were bust by patrolling cops in Kimberley, Northern Cape on Tuesday. “It was just after midday when the flying squad members in Kimberley spotted two men carrying a suspicious looking bag. The men were on foot and approaching a local scrap metal dealer when police stopped and searched them. “They were arrested for possession of suspected stolen goods. “The men, aged 25 and 29, were found with copper weighing 8,3kg and worth about R5 000. “They are expected to appear in the Kimberley Magistrates Court soon.”